I have this happen now and then.  The next time that keg is empty,
remove the keg post and take out the poppet.  Scrub the inside of the
keg post with a small brush.  I use a nice cone shaped on that came with
my turkey baster.  This will get any crud out of the post that might be
blocking the seal.  I also scrub the O-ring on the poppet with an
ordinary washcloth.  This solves the problem 9 times out of 10 for me.
If it still leaks after that you may need to replace the poppet.

Wayne
Bugeater Brewing Company
