On Sat, 28 Apr 2007 20:37:42 +0000 (UTC), <l ... @my.sig> wrote:
> My ball-lock keg has a problem. When I remove the gas line, the gas
> leaks out through the poppet. This just started happenening recently.
> Any ideas on the cause and/or how I can fix this?
">

Either the poppet is dirty (do you take them apart when you clean the keg?),
or the little oring on the poppet is not sitting squarely and won't seal
right.  I've had this happen before, usually taking the post apart (removing
the poppet), cleaning, and re-assembling fixes the problem.  If it still
gives you trouble you may need to replace the poppet.

John.
